      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When you generate a frame, you specify a pose matrix that indicates the device’s",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "position and orientation in the world coordinate space.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "When the device is a head-mounted display, the view for each eye has an additional",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "matrix to specify the position of that eye relative to the device’s pose.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Multiply the device’s pose matrix by the returned matrix to obtain the view’s",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "location in the world coordinate space.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
